{{For|the Don Cherry album|Multikulti (album)}} '''Multikulti''' is a [[slogan]] of the [[multiculturalism]] [[public policy]] approach. Its [[Etymology|etymological]] origin is with the [[Germany|German]] [[Progressivism|progressive]] movements of the 1970s and 1980s.<ref>{{cite news|title= Multicultural mistakes|work= Daily Telegraph|date=2010-10-18|url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/8071854/Multicultural-mistakes.html|accessdate=2010-10-18|location=London}}</ref> It was popularised by the German [[Alliance '90/The Greens|Green Party]] and gained popularity throughout [[Europe]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Merkel says German multicultural society has failed|work= BBC|date=2010-10-17|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-11559451|accessdate=2010-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= The integration debate in Germany: Is multi-kulti dead? |work= [[The Economist]]|date=2010-10-22|url= https://www.economist.com/blogs/newsbook/2010/10/integration_debate_germany|accessdate=2012-05-20}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|title= Multikulti breeds distrust in Germany |work= [[Russia Today]]|date=|url= http://www.rt.com/news/islam-germany-schools-religion-953/|accessdate=2012-05-20}}</ref>
