{{Infobox film | name = The Mask You Live In | image = The Mask You Live In.png | alt = | caption = Film poster | film name = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} --> | director = [[Jennifer Siebel Newsom]] | producer = Jennifer Siebel Newsom | writer = Jennifer Siebel Newsom | screenplay = | story = | based on = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} --> | starring = | narrator = | music = | cinematography = | editing = | studio = <!-- or: | production companies = --> | distributor = <!-- or: | distributors = --> | released = [[2015 in film|2015]] | runtime = <!-- {{Duration|h=|m=|s=}} --> | country = [[United States]] | language = English | budget = | gross = }} '''''The Mask You Live In''''' is a 2015 documentary film written, directed, and produced by [[Jennifer Siebel Newsom]]. It premiered at the [[2015 Sundance Film Festival]]. The film explores what Newsom perceives to be harmful notions about [[masculinity]] in Western culture.
==Background== Newsom's inspiration for making the film came from becoming pregnant with her son.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|title=Sundance:'The Mask You Live In' Examines America’s Boy Crisis|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/sundance-the-mask-you-live-in-examines-americas-boy-crisis-1201412965/|accessdate=January 30, 2015|date=January 23, 2015}}</ref> In an interview she said, "It was really important to me that I could nurture a son who could be true to his authentic self, who wouldn't always feel like he had to prove his masculinity. There's so much loneliness, pain, and suffering when one is pretending to be someone that they're not."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mechanic|first1=Michael|title="Be a Man." What Does That Even Mean?|url=https://www.motherjones.com/environment/2015/01/jennifer-seibel-newsom-mask-you-live-in-masculinity|website=Mother Jones|accessdate=January 30, 2015}}</ref> Newsom raised $101,111 on [[Kickstarter]] towards making the film.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Newsom|first1=Jennifer Siebel|title=The Mask You Live In|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/jensiebelnewsom/the-mask-you-live-in|website=Kickstarter|accessdate=January 30, 2015}}</ref>
==Reception== The film was received slightly positively by critics and currently holds a 60% on Rotten Tomatoes.<ref>{{Citation|title=The Mask You Live In|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_mask_you_live_in_2015/|publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=2016-06-29}}</ref> [[Collider (website)|Collider]]'s Matt Goldberg recommended that the film be required viewing in classrooms.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Goldberg|first1=Matt|title=The Mask You Live In Review |url=http://collider.com/the-mask-you-live-in-review/|publisher=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|accessdate=January 30, 2015}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Masculine psychology]] *''[[Miss Representation]]'', a 2011 documentary film by Newsom about the impact of media portrayals of women
